//----------------------------------------------------------------
DNS = data Source Name  //username:password@protocol(address)/dbname?param1=value1&param2=value2
dsn := "user:password@tcp(127.0.0.1:3306)/dbname"

Part	       Explanation
user	       Database ka username
password	   Us username ka password
tcp	           Protocol jo use ho raha hai (tcp â†’ network connection ke liye)
127.0.0.1	   Database ka address (localhost)
3306	       MySQL ka default port number
/dbname	       Jis database ko access karna hai

//----------------------------------------------------------------
Agar tum MySQL se extra settings bhi specify karna chahte ho, toh dsn me query parameters add kar sakte ho.
Example:
dsn := "root:mypassword@tcp(127.0.0.1:3306)/testdb?charset=utf8mb4&parseTime=True&loc=Local"
ðŸ”¹ charset=utf8mb4 â†’ Unicode characters support karega // taaki Unicode characters (jaise emojis, non-English text) support ho sake.
ðŸ”¹ parseTime=True  â†’ Date/Time parsing enable karega //"Parse" ka matlab hota hai kisi data ko read karna, 
													//samajhna aur usko ek structured format me convert karna. like string to integer
ðŸ”¹ loc=Local       â†’ Local timezone use karega


